5) Write a PHP program that displays a different message based on time of day. For
example, a page should display “Good Morning” if it is accessed in the morning.
<?php
date_default_timezone_set('Asia/Kolkata');
$ti = date("G");
if($ti >= 5 && $ti < 12)
echo "Good Morning";
else if($ti > 12 && $ti < 15)
echo "Good Afternoon";
else if($ti >= 16 && $ti < 21)
echo "Good Evening";
else
echo "Good Night";
echo "<br />Time (in 24hr format): $ti";
?>
Output:
Good Morning
Time (in 24hr format): 10
